.TH "xilinx_dpdma_sw_desc_set_dma_addrs" 9 "xilinx_dpdma_sw_desc_set_dma_addrs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xilinx_dpdma_sw_desc_set_dma_addrs \- Set DMA addresses in the descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xilinx_dpdma_sw_desc_set_dma_addrs
.BI "(struct xilinx_dpdma_device *xdev "  ","
.BI "struct xilinx_dpdma_sw_desc *sw_desc "  ","
.BI "struct xilinx_dpdma_sw_desc *prev "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dma_addr[] "  ","
.BI "unsigned int num_src_addr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xdev" 12
DPDMA device
.IP "sw_desc" 12
The software descriptor in which to set DMA addresses
.IP "prev" 12
The previous descriptor
.IP "dma_addr" 12
array of dma addresses
.IP "num_src_addr" 12
number of addresses in \fIdma_addr\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set all the DMA addresses in the hardware descriptor corresponding to \fIdev\fP
from \fIdma_addr\fP. If a previous descriptor is specified in \fIprev\fP, its next
descriptor DMA address is set to the DMA address of \fIsw_desc\fP. \fIprev\fP may be
identical to \fIsw_desc\fP for cyclic transfers.
